description: Returns a list of the audience export jobs.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token value used to access the next page of results.

nested_items.name: audienceExportJobs
nested_items.description: The audience export jobs that match the request.

nested_items.name: createTime
nested_items.description: The time at which the audience export job was created.

nested_items.name: updateTime
nested_items.description: The most recent time at which the audience export job was updated.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the audience export job.

nested_items.name: audienceGenerationJobArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the audience generation job that was exported.

nested_items.name: audienceSize
nested_items.description: The size of the generated audience. Must match one of the sizes in the configured audience model.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: Whether the audience size is defined in absolute terms or as a percentage. You can use the ABSOLUTE  AudienceSize to configure out audience sizes using the count of identifiers in the output. You can use the Percentage  AudienceSize to configure sizes in the range 1-100 percent.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: The description of the audience export job.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the audience export job.

nested_items.name: statusDetails
nested_items.description: Details about the status of a resource.

nested_items.name: statusCode
nested_items.description: The status code that was returned. The status code is intended for programmatic error handling. Clean Rooms ML will not change the status code for existing error conditions.

nested_items.name: message
nested_items.description: The error message that was returned. The message is intended for human consumption and can change at any time. Use the statusCode for programmatic error handling.

nested_items.name: outputLocation
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 bucket where the audience export is stored.
